# Stone House Checkout & Payment Architecture

## Stack & Constraints
- Frontend: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (no React/Vue — keep it that way)
- Backend: Vercel serverless functions (`api/wedding/*.js`) — Node.js CommonJS
- Payment: **Stripe** — Checkout Sessions with embedded Payment Element
- Contract: click-to-agree with full contract text displayed in-page (ESIGN/UETA compliant)
- Email: Resend SDK (already in package.json) for booking confirmations
- Branch: all checkout work stays on `feature/checkout-payment` — do NOT merge to `main` until fully tested

## Stripe Integration Rules
- **Always use Stripe Checkout Sessions** (not raw Payment Intents) — simpler, PCI-compliant, fewer moving parts
- Session `ui_mode: 'embedded'` with `return_url` — keeps user on our domain, no external redirect
- Payment methods: `['card', 'us_bank_account']` — supports both CC and ACH direct debit
- Currency: `usd` only (ACH only works in USD)
- **Create session server-side** in `api/wedding/create-checkout.js` — NEVER put the Stripe secret key in client JS
- Return `clientSecret` to front-end, mount `stripe.initEmbeddedCheckout()` in checkout.html
- Webhook at `api/wedding/webhook.js` — verify signature with `stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()`
- Listen for `checkout.session.completed` to finalize booking and send confirmation emails

## Checkout Flow
1. **Review** — full quote summary (venue, catering, services, taxes, deposit amount owed)
2. **Availability Warning** — bold, prominent, NON-NEGOTIABLE (see below)
3. **Contract** — scrollable rental agreement; typed name + "I Agree" checkbox before payment unlocks
4. **Payment** — embedded Stripe Payment Element (card or ACH)
5. **Confirmation** — success screen after checkout.session.completed webhook fires

## Availability Warning (NON-NEGOTIABLE — must appear above contract AND above payment)
Show this div in both the contract step and the payment step:
  class="availability-warning" with bold text:
  "IMPORTANT: Before submitting payment, you must confirm with Stone House venue management
  that your event date is available. Submitting payment does not guarantee your date."

## Deposit Logic
- Charge 50% deposit at booking; remainder due 30 days before event date
- depositAmount = Math.round(grandTotal * 0.50 * 100)  [Stripe uses cents]
- Pass deposit amount to create-checkout.js; validate server-side — never trust client-submitted totals
- Display both deposit and remaining balance prominently before checkout

## ESIGN Compliance (Contract)
- Show full rental agreement text in a scrollable container before the checkbox
- Require: typed legal name + checkbox "I have read and agree to the Rental Agreement"
- Payment form must be hidden/disabled until checkbox is checked
- Record on submission: ISO timestamp, typed name, IP (from serverless request headers), user-agent
- Pass this data as metadata on the Stripe Checkout Session

## Environment Variables (Vercel Dashboard → Project Settings → Environment Variables)
  STRIPE_SECRET_KEY       — server-side only, never expose to client
  STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY  — safe for client-side JS
  STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET   — for verifying webhook signatures
  RESEND_API_KEY          — already configured

## File Map
  checkout.html                          — booking UI (review → contract → payment)
  src/js/checkout.js                     — client-side checkout logic
  src/css/checkout.css                   — checkout page styles
  api/wedding/create-checkout.js         — Stripe session creator
  api/wedding/webhook.js                 — Stripe webhook handler
  api/wedding/booking-confirmation.js    — confirmation email sender
  CHECKOUT_STRATEGY.md                   — full architecture + decision log

## Security Rules
- Stripe secret key ONLY in serverless functions — never in HTML or client JS
- Validate all booking amounts server-side before creating Stripe session
- Webhook handler MUST verify Stripe signature before any processing
- Use stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(rawBody, sig, secret) — require raw body (not parsed JSON)
